Some effective strategies for avoiding copyright infringement include: 
1. Avoiding materials that are not in the public domain or that do not have the copyright owner’s permission; 
2. Properly crediting sources and obtaining permission when necessary; 
3. Using open source materials and content; 
4. Utilizing fair use guidelines when quoting or paraphrasing; 
5. Avoiding materials that have a copyright symbol or notice; 
6. Staying up to date with the latest copyright laws and trends; 
7. Educating oneself and others on copyright laws and best practices.
